<div class="header">
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    <h1>Prologis (PLD)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of Prologis Inc. — mathematically derived assumptions, and one final number.</p>
    <p class="date">Updated March 18, 2026</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
    <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
    <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${currentPrice !== null ? currentPrice.toFixed(2) : 'N/A'} ({marginOfSafety}%)</div>
    <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
      {verdictText}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${latestRev.toLocaleString()}M</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Latest Revenue</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${latestFCF.toLocaleString()}M</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${latestEPS !== null ? latestEPS.toFixed(2) : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{latestOpMargin !== null ? latestOpMargin + '%' : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Operating Margin</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model, driving value directly from actual reported financial metrics and explicit mathematical derivations based on current risk-free rates.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Start with Base Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>We use <strong>{baseCashFlowLabel}</strong> of ${baseCashFlow.toLocaleString()}M. Prologis is an industrial REIT, meaning it has significant capital expenditures (investments in real estate) that can result in highly volatile or negative Free Cash Flow. In our valuation, we utilize the proxy that most accurately reflects ongoing cash generation capability.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
      <p>We apply a mathematically derived compound annual growth rate (CAGR) from the company's past performance to project Phase 1. For Prologis, the calculated historical growth rate establishes our baseline moving forward.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
      <p>Using the Gordon Growth Model, we assign a terminal growth rate permanently tied to a fraction of the 10-year Treasury yield, reflecting long-term sustainable growth equivalent to baseline economic expansion.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
      <p>Future cash flows are discounted by a dynamically computed WACC based on the 10Y Treasury and Prologis's specific Beta.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
      <p>Enterprise Value + Net Cash = Equity Value. Divide by outstanding shares to discover the final per-share intrinsic value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>Core Assumptions</h2>

  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Derived directly from the company's historical CAGR over the last 5 years. This mathematically reflects the proven growth trajectory rather than relying on fabricated forward estimates. Capped to prevent unrealistic exponential runoffs.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Calculated using CAPM: Risk-Free Rate (10Y Treasury at 4.18%) + Beta ({beta !== null ? beta : '1.0'}) × ERP (Derived conservatively at 4.18%). This strictly mathematically aligns the required return with current macroeconomic reality.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Tethered strictly to a proxy of the long-term risk-free rate, ensuring the perpetuity growth assumes a maturing company matching broader macro-economic expansion levels.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

