  <!-- ═══ FAQ & RISKS ═══ -->
  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <div class="faq">
    <details>
      <summary>How does the nature of Prologis as a REIT affect the DCF?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">As an industrial REIT, Prologis naturally runs high capital expenditures due to real estate acquisitions and developments. This depresses Free Cash Flow significantly relative to their Operating Cash Flow. If FCF turns negative or highly volatile, using Operating Cash Flow as a proxy in the DCF might yield more normalized valuations. Our model adapts to the base cash flows scraped.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Where do the Beta and 10Y Treasury yield come into play?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">They act as explicit mathematical foundations. The 10Y Treasury (4.18%) provides the risk-free rate, and Beta calculates the proportional specific risk premium (ERP). This aligns our discount rate structurally to reality instead of arbitrary estimations.</div>
    </details>
  </div>

